t%20there.%26quot%3B%20Artificial%20intelligence%20alone%20won't%20get%20the%20job%20done%20right%20now.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHuman%20oversight%20is%20still%20heavily%20required%2C%20but%20a%20shift%20is%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20autonomy%20may%20be%20deeply%20overhyped%20today%2C%20it%20may%20be%20completely%20unavoidable%20tomorrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArk%20is%20working%20on%20more%20autonomous%20tech%2C%20and%20expects%20rapid%20improvements%20in%20the%20area.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20already%20are%20past%20the%20point%20of%20no%20return%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CEO%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20current%20battlefield%20shows%20%26quot%3Bautonomy%20is%20necessary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20hands%20can%20be%20seen%20holding%20a%20controller%20that%20connects%20to%20a%20laptop%20that%20is%20sat%20on%20top%20of%20a%20robot%20with%20four%20large%20black%20wheels%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6931b6a87ecd1d1da662ede7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221477%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkraine's%20Ark%20Robotics%20makes%20autonomous%20systems%2C%20and%20is%20developing%20a%20system%20that%20can%20control%20thousands%20of%20robots.%3Cp%3EArk%20Robotics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EArk%20Robotics%20makes%20a%20suite%20of%20autonomous%20robots%20used%20by%20more%20than%2020%20Ukrainian%20brigades%2C%20and%20is%20developing%20a%20system%20that%20allows%20thousands%20of%20aerial%20drones%20and%20ground%20robots%2C%20including%20ones%20made%20by%20different%20companies%2C%20to%20work%20together%20with%20minimal%20human%20involvement.%20The%20system%2C%20Frontier%2C%20isn't%20fully%20autonomous%2C%20nor%20does%20it%20claim%20to%20be.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20where%20the%20industry%20is%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20Achi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20autonomy%20is%20present%20in%20Frontier%20but%20described%20it%20as%20an%20early%20step%20toward%20network-level%20autonomy%20at%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTime%20is%20essential%2C%26quot%3B%20Achi%20explained.%20%26quot%3BDemocratic%20countries%20aren't%20the%20only%20ones%20racing%20to%20build%20such%20products.%20We're%20doing%20our%20best%2C%20supported%20by%20our%20team's%20strong%20autonomy%20expertise%20and%20continuous%20feedback%20from%20the%20front%20line.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22670b614a-5cc9-4e73-a4fc-55f2899c830a%5C%22%3EThe%20autonomy%20question%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAutonomous%20systems%20have%20become%20increasingly%20common%20in%20Ukraine%20as%20domestic%20companies%20and%20Western%20allies%20bolster%20its%20fight%20against%20Russia's%20invasion%2C%20now%20close%20to%20entering%20its%20fourth%20year.%20These%20systems%20help%20offset%20Russia's%20larger%20force%20size%2C%20reduce%20demands%20on%20operators%2C%20and%20keep%20drone%20pilots%20farther%20from%20danger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAutonomous%20systems%20make%20decisions%20faster%20than%20humans%20and%20handle%20certain%20routine%20battlefield%20tasks%2C%20freeing%20troops%20to%20focus%20on%20higher-level%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20what%20is%20described%20as%20autonomous%20still%20requires%20heavy%20human%20involvement.%20Part%20of%20the%20issue%20is%20definitional%20%E2%80%94%20autonomy%20can%20describe%20everything%20from%20basic%20navigation%20to%20a%20system%20that%20identifies%2C%20classifies%2C%20and%20acts%20on%20a%20target%20without%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221299%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20grey%20robot%20with%20four%20large%20black%20wheels%20on%20a%20dirt%20ground%20with%20trees%20behind%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6931b7e504d0f0a114f168ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22867%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArk%20Robotics%20makes%20a%20series%20of%20ground%20robots%2C%20including%20its%20M4%20model.%3Cp%3EArk%20Robotics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20advanced%20systems%20might%20launch%20a%20weapon%20autonomously%20or%20coordinate%20a%20drone%20swarm.%20Others%20can%20learn%20and%20make%20decisions%20themselves%2C%20but%20many%20still%20keep%20humans%20in%20the%20loop%20for%20both%20ethical%20and%20policy%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarfare%20experts%20say%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bautonomous%26quot%3B%20is%20often%20used%20inconsistently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20report%20from%20the%20UK's%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20last%20year%20noted%20that%20there%20is%20no%20agreed-upon%20definition%20for%20how%20autonomous%20an%20%26quot%3Bautonomous%26quot%3B%20system%20actually%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKateryna%20Bondar%2C%20an%20AI%20and%20defense%20expert%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fukraines-future-vision-and-current-capabilities-waging-ai-enabled-autonomous-warfare%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20%26quot%3Bfully%20autonomous%20warfare%20remains%20an%20aspiration%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20progress%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20made%20in%20partial%20autonomy%2C%20especially%20with%20drone%20tech.%20In%20Ukraine%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bautonomous%26quot%3B%20is%20often%20used%20interchangeably%20with%20%26quot%3Bunmanned%2C%26quot%3B%20even%20if%20only%20limited%20autonomy%20is%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22274e3a4c-e6bd-440e-b056-c7b5a33c3017%5C%22%3EChasing%20autonomy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAchi%20said%20his%20company%20is%20pursuing%20autonomy%20on%20two%20levels.%20The%20first%20is%20edge%20autonomy%2C%20where%20systems%20make%20decisions%20on%20their%20own%20without%20instructions%20from%20an%20operator%20or%20control%20center.%20He%20gave%20the%20example%20of%20an%20aerial%20drone%20scouting%20an%20area%2C%20waiting%20for%20a%20target%2C%20able%20to%20act%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20level%2C%20which%20Ark%20is%20more%20interested%20in%2C%20is%20the%20orchestration%20layer%2C%20where%20multiple%20drones%20or%20robots%20coordinate%20and%20give%20tasks.%20Achi%20said%20this%20level%20is%20where%20you%20can%20give%20the%20system%20%26quot%3Ban%20abstract%20task%2C%26quot%3B%20like%20protecting%20a%20perimeter%2C%20and%20it%20can%20then%20%26quot%3Borchestrate%20whatever%20is%20needed%20to%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20directing%20systems%20such%20as%20strike%20drones.%20Humans%20can%20step%20in%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20second%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20hardest%20to%20solve%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20needs%20a%20good%20edge%20foundation%20to%20build%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrontier%2C%20Ark's%20AI-powered%20system%2C%20is%20designed%20to%20coordinate%20thousands%20of%20uncrewed%20systems%2C%20sharply%20reducing%20operator%20demands%20and%20keeping%20humans%20much%20farther%20from%20combat.%20In%20a%20demonstration%20in%20Denmark%2C%20a%20user%20remotely%20operated%20a%20ground%20robot%201%2C200%20miles%20away%20in%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArk%2C%20founded%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20now%20headquartered%20in%20NATO%20member%20Estonia%2C%20aims%20to%20keep%20humans%20involved%20as%20little%20as%20needed%20so%20decisions%20can%20be%20made%20much%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22755786b2-7590-477e-8b23-bc66050b1dd3%5C%22%3EAn%20autonomous%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWestern%20militaries%20and%20companies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20rivals%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20are%20pushing%20for%20more%20autonomous%20systems.%20NATO%20is%20prioritizing%20autonomous%20technology%2C%20particularly%20in%20drone%20technology%2C%20for%20threat%20detection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20many%20lines%20of%20effort%20are%20programs%20like%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense's%20push%20for%20all-domain%20attritable%20autonomous%20systems%20through%20the%20Replicator%20initiative%20and%20the%20UK's%20substantial%20investment%20this%20year%20of%20more%20than%20%245%20billion%20in%20uncrewed%20autonomous%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20far%20autonomy%20can%20go%20technologically%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%2C%20and%20its%20use%20may%20be%20limited%20by%20ethical%20debates.%20As%20is%2C%20Western%20militaries%20often%20restrict%20higher%20levels%20of%20autonomy%20in%20lethal%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Achi%20said%20there%20won't%20be%20any%20turning%20back%2C%20and%20expects%20all%20militaries%20to%20be%20using%20it%20in%20some%20form.%20He%20said%20autonomy%20has%20become%20%26quot%3Bkind%20of%20prerequisite%20to%20be%20successful%20in%20the%20total%20drone%20warfare%20that%20is%20coming%20to%20all%20of%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20have%20all%20these%20fancy%20drones%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20what%20is%20the%20use%20of%20them%20if%20you%20can't%20really%20deploy%20them%20at%20scale%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fautonomy-defense-overhyped-past-point-of-no-return-ukraine-company-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1764931506000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6931b73e7ecd1d1da662edfe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fautonomy-defense-overhyped-past-point-of-no-return-ukraine-company-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Defense%20forces%20%26quot%3Bwant%20a%20hundred%20percent%20reliability%20and%20the%20AI%20is%20just%20not%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Ark%20Robotics'%20founder%20and%20CEO%20told%20Business%20Insider.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbaker%40insider.com%20(Sin%C3%A9ad%20Baker)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fautonomy-defense-overhyped-past-point-of-no-return-ukraine-company-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SKF%20India%20Industrial%20expec