2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Austin%20Dean%20was%20earning%20his%20various%20financial%20advisor%20certifications%2C%20he%20wasn't%20fully%20satisfied%20with%20the%20curriculum%20that%20revolved%20around%20traditional%20wisdom%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20the%20advice%20to%20max%20out%20retirement%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20in%20his%20early%2020s%20at%20the%20time%20and%20personally%20interested%20in%20the%20financial%20independence%20movement.%20The%20thought%20of%20%26quot%3Blocking%20up%26quot%3B%20his%20savings%20in%20accounts%20that%20wouldn't%20be%20accessible%20until%20age%2059%20%C2%BD%20wasn't%20appealing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'There's%20got%20to%20be%20a%20better%20way.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20have%20to%20wait%20until%20I'm%2060%20to%20be%20able%20to%20feel%20like%20I%20have%20the%20financial%20flexibility%20to%20do%20the%20things%20I%20want%20to%20do%2C'%26quot%3B%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwaystoneadvisors.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWaystone%20Advisors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20RIA%20firm%20that%20specializes%20in%20helping%20people%20achieve%20financial%20independence%20in%20non-traditional%20ways%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20started%20digging%20into%20what%20the%20top%201%25%20do%20%E2%80%94%20and%20their%20strategies%20were%20entirely%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20wealthy%20don't%20get%20there%20by%20maximizing%20their%20401(k)s%20and%20making%20coffee%20at%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dean%2C%20who%20has%20ChFC%2C%20CLU%2C%20CFP%2C%20and%20RICP%20designations.%20%26quot%3BThey%20started%20businesses%2C%20they%20bought%20businesses%2C%20they%20invested%20in%20real%20estate%2C%20they%20prioritized%20cash%20flow%2C%20they%20became%20the%20bank.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b2be5d7-1879-487a-831e-373099eeb3cf%5C%22%3EAvoiding%20'money%20jail'%20through%20non-traditional%20investment%20strategies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDean%20refers%20to%20retirement-specific%20accounts%20such%20as%20401(k)%20plans%20and%20IRAs%20as%20%26quot%3Bmoney%20jail.%26quot%3B%20They're%20excellent%20savings%20vehicles%20with%20strong%20tax%20benefits%2C%20but%20you%20typically%20can't%20access%20your%20contributions%20without%20incurring%20a%2010%25%20fee%20until%20you%20reach%20age%2059%20%C2%BD.%20This%20rule%20is%20in%20place%20to%20encourage%20individuals%20to%20keep%20their%20retirement%20money%20invested%2C%20rather%20than%20dipping%20into%20it%20for%20short-term%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20consequence%20of%20maxing%20out%20tax-deferred%20retirement%20accounts%20may%20arise%20years%20later%20when%20you%20must%20start%20withdrawing%20from%20them%20in%20your%2070s%20%E2%80%94%20the%20IRS%20calls%20these%20required%20minimum%20distributions%20(RMDs)%2C%20and%20they're%20calculated%20based%20on%20your%20account%20balance%20and%20life%20expectancy.%20If%20you%20don't%20start%20taking%20RMDs%2C%20you%20could%20incur%20a%2025%25%20penalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20IRS%20very%20reasonably%20says%2C%20'We%20haven't%20gotten%20our%20piece%20of%20that%2C'%20and%20you%20need%20to%20start%20pulling%20that%20money%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%20However%2C%20if%20you've%20been%20fiscally%20savvy%20and%20built%20income%20streams%20that%20provide%20enough%20cash%20flow%20to%20live%20on%20without%20needing%20the%20retirement%20account%20funds%2C%20you're%20%26quot%3Bunfortunately%20stuck%20in%20this%20position%20of%20having%20to%20pull%20that%20money%20out%20anyway%20and%20then%20pay%20taxes%20on%20it.%20Retirement%20accounts%20take%20away%20our%20control%20and%20put%20it%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20IRS.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDean%20isn't%20discouraging%20saving%20for%20retirement%3B%20he%20just%20believes%20there's%20a%20more%20efficient%20way%20to%20save%20that%20gives%20investors%2C%20particularly%20those%20interested%20in%20early%20retirement%2C%20more%20control%20and%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22austin%20dean%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69326a387ecd1d1da662fbf6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAustin%20Dean%20is%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Waystone%20Advisors.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Austin%20Dean%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20non-traditional%20solution%20he%20provides%20for%20his%20clients%20is%20to%20obtain%20a%20securities-backed%20line%20of%20credit%20(SBLOC).%20This%20is%20a%20type%20of%20loan%20in%20which%20an%20investor%20uses%20their%20stock%20portfolio%20or%20other%20assets%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-loans-art-yachts-real-estate-investing-private-banks-2021-11%3Fr%3Dwealthtax-teaser%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20their%20fine%20art%20and%20luxury%20yachts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20collateral.%20It%20allows%20for%20quick%20access%20to%20cash%20without%20having%20to%20sell%20investments%20and%20trigger%20a%20capital%20gains%20tax%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20investor%20can%20then%20pump%20that%20cash%20into%20other%20investments%2C%20such%20as%20starting%20a%20business%20or%20purchasing%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20your%20money%20is%20doing%20two%20things%20at%20the%20same%20time%3A%20It's%20in%20the%20market%2C%20and%20it's%20being%20used%20for%20other%20wealth-building%20tools%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20risk%20is%20pulling%20out%20too%20much%20money%2C%20and%20the%20stock%20market%20crashes%2C%20he%20explained%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20recommend%20always%20leaving%20a%20buffer%20between%20what%20you%20are%20approved%20for%20and%20what%20is%20being%20used.%20I%20also%20recommend%20having%20other%20liquid%20assets%20or%20lines%20of%20credit%20in%20reserve%2C%20in%20case%20the%20market%20takes%20an%20unexpected%20swing.%20But%20if%20someone%20has%20an%20account%20that%20is%20properly%20diversified%2C%20leaves%20a%2020%25%20buffer%20on%20their%20line%20of%20credit%2C%20and%20has%20other%20flexible%20and%20uncorrelated%20assets%2C%20they%20should%20be%20able%20to%20weather%20meaningful%20market%20volatility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESBLOCs%20are%20popular%20among%20high-net-worth%20individuals.%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%26quot%3Bused%20a%20line%20of%20credit%20on%20his%20Tesla%20stock%20to%20go%20and%20buy%20Twitter%20and%20create%20X%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20Dean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20individuals%20with%20five-figure%20savings%20can%20also%20benefit%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20somebody%20has%20as%20little%20as%20%2450%2C000%20to%20%2460%2C000%20in%20an%20investment%20account%2C%20we%20can%20help%20them%20set%20up%20a%20securities-backed%20line%20of%20credit%20for%20like%20%2435%2C000%20to%20%2440%2C000.%20Then%20they%20can%20use%20that%20to%20go%20buy%20their%20first%20rental%20property.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20use%20an%20SBLOC%2C%20this%20strategy%20may%20not%20be%20for%20you%2C%20he%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BFirst%20and%20foremost%2C%20figure%20out%20what%20your%20goals%20are.%20If%20your%20goal%20is%20to%20have%20a%20bunch%20of%20money%20in%20retirement%20accounts%20at%2060%20or%2065%2C%20then%20keep%20doing%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20noted%20that%20he%20doesn't%20advise%20clients%20who%20already%20have%20a%20sizable%20nest%20egg%20tied%20up%20in%20retirement%20accounts%20to%20liquidate%20and%20incur%20penalties.%20But%2C%20if%20they're%20looking%20to%20achieve%20financial%20independence%20and%20retire%20early%2C%20he%20typically%20recommends%20lowering%20their%20contributions%20to%20just%20enough%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20a%20401(k)%20match%2C%20which%20is%20essentially%20free%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20strategy%20he%20discusses%20with%20clients%20is%20funding%20a%20self-directed%20IRA%2C%20which%20allows%20them%20to%20invest%20in%20alternatives%20inside%20their%20IRA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20younger%20the%20person%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20we%20are%20to%20not%20use%20a%20self-directed%20IRA%20because%20we'd%20rather%20have%20their%20money%20not%20in%20'money%20jail'%20and%20able%20to%20do%20two%20or%20more%20things%20at%20once%20with%20an%20SBLOC%20or%20well-designed%20whole%20life%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20But%20for%20clients%20in%20their%2050s%20or%20older%20with%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20money%20in%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20self-directed%20IRA%20is%20a%20way%20for%20them%20to%20access%20unique%20alternative%20investments%20to%20help%20diversify%20their%20assets%20and%20create%20income%20without%20needed%20to%20liquidate%20their%20retirement%20accounts%20and%20pay%20taxes%20and%20penalties.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDean%20understands%20that%20non-traditional%20planning%20isn't%20for%20everyone%2C%20but%20wants%20investors%20to%20understand%20all%20of%20their%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20find%20the%20traditional%20wisdom%20of%20'you%20should%20max%20fund%20your%20401(k)%20or%20your%20IRA'%20to%20be%20damaging%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20come%20to%20us%2C%20and%20they're%20like%2C%20'OK%2C%20I%20want%20financial%20independence%2C'%20but%20then%20realize%20all%20of%20the%20money%20they've%20been%20working%20hard%20to%20save%2C%20they%20can't%20access%20without%20giving%20up%20at%20least%2010%25%20plus%20taxes%20%E2%80%94%20that%20can%20be%20really%20disheartening.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-investment-ideas-financial-independence-retire-early-retirement-wealth-planning-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1764930682000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69320fda04d0f0a114f17486%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fw